/* PairShot iOS — English strings (P9.3)
 *
 * First-pass machine-quality translations. The roadmap explicitly
 * defers final translation polish to P10 (TestFlight Prep). Until then
 * these provide sufficient coverage for QA on an English-locale device
 * without falling back to Korean for every label.
 *
 * Maintenance:
 * - Keys MUST match `ko.lproj/Localizable.strings` 1:1.
 *   `LocalizableKeysAuditTests` enforces parity at build time.
 * - Format specifiers (%@, %d, %d%%) must remain in the same order
 *   per Apple's positional argument rules — Swift `String(format:)`
 *   crashes on mismatched %@/%d.
 */

